# Fun Kit Rock-Paper-Scissors Game

## Project Description
This project is a Rock-Paper-Scissors game implemented on the Fun Kit hardware platform. It allows two players to duel by selecting rock, paper, or scissors using the top, left, and right buttons on two separate Fun Kits. The winner and loser of each round are displayed on the LED screen at the end of the game.

## Technologies Used
- **Programming Language:** C
- **Platform:** Embedded system (Fun Kit)

## Features
- **Two-player gameplay:** Utilizes separate Fun Kit devices for each player.
- **Input handling:** Players use physical buttons to select rock, paper, or scissors.
- **Results display:** The winner of each round is shown on the Fun Kit's LED screen.

## Installation Instructions
To install and run the game on your Fun Kit devices, follow these steps:
1. Ensure the Fun Kit development environment is set up on your system.
2. Clone the repository to your local machine:
   ```
   git clone https://github.com/yangzhangnz/ENCE260.git
   git clone https://eng-git.canterbury.ac.nz/ence260-2023/group_510.git
   ```
3. Compile the project using the appropriate commands for the Fun Kit platform.
4. Upload the compiled program to each Fun Kit device.

## Usage
1. Start the game by powering on both Fun Kit devices.
2. Each player selects rock, paper, or scissors using the top, left, or right buttons on their respective devices.
3. The game evaluates the choices and displays the results on the LED screen.
4. Repeat the process for multiple rounds.

## Configuration
No additional configuration is required to play the game.

